      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And afterwards he built an outer wall to the city of David westward unto Gihon in the ravine.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Manasseh completed the wall begun by Hezekiah (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Chronicles 32:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). This highly circumstantial account of the public works undertaken by Manasseh after his restoration, is utterly unlike fiction, and almost compels the assumption of a real historical source, no longer extant, from which the whole section has been derived.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Even to the entering in of the fish gate.—The fish-gate lay near the north-east corner of the lower city (Nehemiah 3:3). The direction of the outer wall is described first westward, and then eastward.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Even",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "to",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "the entering in of the fish gate.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—The fish-gate lay near the north-east corner of the lower city (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Nehemiah 3:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "). The direction of the outer wall is described first westward, and then eastward.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And compassed about Ophel.—And surrounded the Ophel (mound); seil., with the wall, which he carried on from the north-east to the south-east. Uzziah and Jotham had already worked upon these fortifications (2Chronicles 26:9; 2Chronicles 27:3). Manasseh now finished them, “raising them up to a very great height.”",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "compassed about Ophel.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "And surrounded the Ophel",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (mound); seil., with the wall, which he carried on from the north-east to the south-east. Uzziah and Jotham had already worked upon these fortifications (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Chronicles 26:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Chronicles 27:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "). Manasseh now finished them, “raising them up to a very great height.”",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Raised it—i.e., the outer wall.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Raised it",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "i.e.,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " the outer wall.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And put captains of war.—(Comp. 2Chronicles 17:2; 2Chronicles 32:6.) Literally, captains of an army ( sārê chayil).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "put captains of war.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—(Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Chronicles 17:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
