  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Now after this he built a wall without the city of David,.... Which perhaps had been broken down by the Assyrian army, when it came and took him; Vitringa (l) thinks this is the wall of the pool of Siloah, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 3:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " which seems to be the first and oldest wall, as Josephus (m); for that turning to the north bent towards the pool of Siloam; an Arabic writer (n) calls it the southern wall: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "on the west side of Gihon; on the west side of the city, towards Gihon; for that was to the west of it, 2 Chronicles 32:30, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "on the west side of Gihon; on the west side of the city, towards Gihon; for that was to the west of it, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 32:30",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "in the valley, even to the entering in at the fish gate; through which the fish were brought from Joppa, and where, according to the Targum, they were sold: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and compassed about Ophel; the eastern part of Mount Zion; some say it was the holy of holies, 2 Chronicles 27:3, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and compassed about Ophel; the eastern part of Mount Zion; some say it was the holy of holies, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 27:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and raised it up a very great height; built the wall very high there: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and put captains of war in all the fenced cities of Judah; this he did to put his kingdom in a posture of defence, should it be attacked by the Assyrian army again. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(l) Comment. in Jesaiam, c. 22. 9. (m) De Bello Jud. l. 5. c. 4. sect. 9. (n) Abulpharag. Hist. Dynast. Dyn. 3. p. 67. ",
