  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 14.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The wall without",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; or, Revised Version, the outer ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "wall, is",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " probably one with that of Hezekiah (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 32:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), which now Manasseh repairs, or rebuilds, and perhaps lengthens as well as heightens. The fish gate (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 13:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), left on the north of Jerusalem, and opened on the main road for the sea (Conder's 'Handbook,' etc., p. 343). The wall traversed the north and east sides to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Ophel",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", \"on the wall\" of which, it is said (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 27:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), \"Jotham built much.\" Hezekiah also built much there, and now Manasseh ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "raised it up a very great height.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " 2 Chronicles 33:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
